Package de.sbtab.services

Enum TableType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TableType>
      • de.sbtab.services.TableType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<TableType>
    public enum TableType
extends java.lang.Enum<TableType>
    Represents a type of SBTabTable view

    If a new name to appropriate table should be assigned, the following naming rules must be observed: 

     1. If a name consists of several words every space(blank) should be substituted with
          underscore(_)
 
     2. Every separate type must be written in upper case(general conventions)

    Why naming rules are important?

    The SBTabTabsComposer creates new tabs based on the name of the jfx TextLabel of corresponding TreeItem in TreeView. The name of the Tab is translated into the corresponding TableType, depending on that SBTabTableProducer generates necessary TableView for displaying it in the Tab.
